# Frontend Standards

- Read `packages/frontend/AGENTS.md` before frontend work.
- Prefer existing `@n8n/design-system` components, composables, stores, and semantic tokens before creating new primitives.
- Use semantic tokens from design-system stylesheets; avoid hardcoded spacing, colors, or legacy tokens in new code.
- All user-facing text must go through `@n8n/i18n`.
- Preserve keyboard access, visible focus, labels, dialog semantics, and screen reader affordances.
- Use icon names from `updatedIconSet`; do not introduce deprecated icons.
- Keep Pinia state changes narrow and check for unused computed properties after store changes.
- For changed UI, verify at least one critical interaction and check console/network failures.
